title: Clover
creator: Susan Coolidge
description: LibriVox recording of Clover, by Susan Coolidge. Read by Elli. Clover is the fourth book in the popular What Katy Did series. After Katy's wedding, the focus shifts to her little sister Clover. Their brother Phil encounters serious illness in the winter, and Dr. Carr sends him with Clover to the mountains of Colorado. Clarence Page, their naughty cousin from the other books, lives nearby. He is a rancher now with an attractive English partner, Geoff Templestowe, whom Clover falls for. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: LibriVox; audiobook; teen; romance; fiction; children; susan coolidge; Clover; What Katy did; Katy Carr
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
Thanks for making this book available.

 The reader is exellent. She has a bit of an accent but it is perfect for the book.
I loved the book and I also liked the reader!
